definitions.definition: Out of or beyond the power or authority of a court or judge; beyond jurisdiction .
examples: An extrajudicial conveyance is effected by the act of the parties and does not involve, as in the fine and recovery, judicial proceedings.

main_definition: ( law ) Out of or beyond the power or authority of a court or judge; beyond jurisdiction .
secondary_definitions: ( law , of a punishment ) Carried out without legal authority .
